This is an embedded output of all my tweets, posts, and whatnot. Occasionally I'll cross post so I've just added the most appropriate outreach method of the content

Any entomologically well versed people know what #insect I'm seeing here on this Syncarpia? Heard it's a gall mites of some sort pic.twitter.com/91wHZRIaRO

--- Karina Guo (she/her) (@dandy_gumnut) July 22, 2023
```{=html} ```

Amazing symposium on weeds and genetics. Who knew the Lantana complex was made of \~20 species of varying morphology and aggressiveness?? Everyone always only talks about it being L. camara! üèµÔ∏è @p_luirving pic.twitter.com/z01PApko7z

--- Karina Guo (she/her) (@dandy_gumnut) July 14, 2023

Our leaf masking model isn't perfect... That's why we got another model (a leaf classifier) to flag these leaves as 'invalid'. That allowed us to get rid of those pesky half leaves, and increasing our workflow's accuracy! pic.twitter.com/ZnRHCkMAVH

--- Karina Guo (she/her) (@dandy_gumnut) July 2, 2023
```{=html} ```

Here's what my machine learning model does. It finds the pixels of leaves on the herbarium sheets. This saves me from having to measure it's leaf by hand, one by one. In turn, I get a massive dataset (50x the size of original datasets!). pic.twitter.com/ooubsMXenV

--- Karina Guo (she/her) (@dandy_gumnut) June 30, 2023
```{=html} ```
